Table.PRT_Q: What is the reading mainly about?
Table.PRT_CHOICE1: A bad sleeping habit is getting up late on the weekends.
Table.PRT_CHOICE2: Children need enough sleep, and there are ways to get it.
Table.PRT_CHOICE3: Students can improve their grades by studying more and sleeping less.
Table.PRT_CHOICE4: Kids don’t get enough sleep because they worry about school work.

Table.PRT_Q: Why is sleeping eight hours or more important?
Table.PRT_CHOICE4: It helps you wake up early.

Table.PRT_Q: What does NOT help you sleep?
Table.PRT_CHOICE2: Keeping the bedroom dark at night
Table.PRT_CHOICE3: Making your room bright in the morning
Table.PRT_CHOICE4: Going to bed at different times every night
